'''''Star Wars'' 47''' is the forty-seventh issue in the [[Star Wars (1977)|''Marvel Star Wars'']] series of comics.

==Plot summary==
The [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] have captured a damaged new model of [[Imperial warbot]] on [[Xeron]] and decide to ask the assistance of the droid populated space station known as [[Kligson's Moon/Legends|Kligson's Moon]] in repairing the droid so the Alliance technicians can study it. [[Kligson/Legends|Kligson]] agrees to repair the droid, but [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] must accompany the warbot to observe the operation since Kligson intends to keep the droid after it's repaired. However, another droid on Kligson's moon has other ideas as the former Imperial [[Z-X3 experimental droid trooper]], [[Z-X3|Zee-Exthree]], plans to use parts of the warbot to repair his own war droid and lead a revolt against Kligson. But Kligson had anticipated this and sent a decoy to lure the Zee-Exthree and his followers out into the open when he would launch his own warbot against them. With the battle over, R2-D2 and C-3PO record the schematics of the warbot and return to the Rebels, while Kligson moves his station from its current orbit to a more secret location where the Empire cannot find it.

==Continuity==
*This issue was later adapted into a book-and-record titled ''[[The Further Adventures: Droid World]]'', released by [[Buena Vista Records]].
*A typo on page 15 spells "Tagge" as "Taage".

